1
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:11,080
The synthesis test goes as follows: In a test room you can sit on a chair.

2
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:15,920
You will see a painting, then you should hold for your left eye-

3
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:21,160
- And read a row from left to right.
 When done, you have to change your hand and eye-

4
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:25,800
- And hold for your right eye and read the same row from the right.

5
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:30,120
When you are done, you can read a line with both eyes.

6
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:35,560
If you have lenses or glasses, you bring them so we can use them during the synthesis test.

7
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:40,080
If you use night lenses, you may not have them a week before trial.

8
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:45,600
If you have impaired vision, bring a current prescription from the optician.

9
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:50,760
In the color release test, we check your color vision.

10
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:57,680
You will see numbers with clearly different color.
 One, two or no numbers.

11
00:00:57,840 --> 00:01:00,640
You have three seconds per painting.

12
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:05,720
During the hearing test you can sit in a soundproof hearing cage.

13
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:12,200
During the hearing test you have a pair of hearing aids on you, the red should be on the right ear.

14
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:17,400
In the test you will hear both bright high tones and low dull tones.

15
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:20,640
You press the button immediately when you hear a ton.

16
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:25,680
We check one ear at a time and the test starts on your right ear.

